           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> there are 8 main techniques or methods how a nec can kill a mob solo.<br /><br />1. Assist pet<br />2. Fear Kite<br />3. Root Dot<br />4. Pet tank & heal<br />5. Pet tank & slow undead<br />6. Aggo Kite<br />7. Charm kite<br />8. Lifetap tank<br />9. (enlighten me please)<br /><br />you can combine these techniques like starting root dot and go forward with aggo kite, but thats not one of the original main methods.<br /><br />we necs are probably the only class who got 8 ways to death.<br /><br />if anybody likes to write a guide (or did already, pls link), how to do one of these techniques, i will combine them all and put it in the guide section. of cause everybody will get named as an author.<br /><br />if not i will do the very best by myself.<br /><br />for option 8 some uber guy like Yags should explain, even if i am sure i will find yags guide via search)<br /><br />just an idea, how this could look like:<br /><br />2. Fear Kiting<br /><br />in general:<br /><br />a. pull a mob to your camp where pet is waiting<br />b. send pet, snare mob, fear mob<br />c. add dots<br />d. sit and med<br />e. keep mob snared an feared<br /><br />preparation:<br /><br />- buff your pet, just if fear breaks and it has to tank<br />- keep something memmed for crowd control, root comes to mind.<br /><br />a. pull<br /><br />some options here:<br />- pull with darkness if you like to kill casual and there is no need to get the mob fast out of an dangerous (ADD) area. dooming is nice, higher snare dots just if you need the dmg)<br />- pull with low dmg just to ensure, that your pet gets aggo later immediately and you got time to cast fear or snare casually. lvl 1 lifetap, splurt (1st tick just 12 dmg growing) and item procs come to mind)<br />- pull with high aggo spells, if you like to mix fear and aggo kiting (see below)<br /><br />b. fear mob<br /><br />some options here:<br />- if you use a strong pet, send pet and try to fear, even to snare 1st if unsnared pulled<br />- if you use a weak pet (like a rog), its a good idea to have pulled snared and send pet while you cast fear. even later, just if mob is definatrly feared.<br /><br />c. add dots<br /><br />- its not the best idea to add all your dots, thats mostly not efficient in terms of mana<br />- use just a few of your most manaefficient dots and let the pet work.<br />- you even can fearkite without any dot, just with a pet, but thats mostly to slow.<br /><br />d/e. sit and med, resnare refear<br /><br />- try to sit and med as long as you can<br />- on the other side, if mob runs too far away you cant help your pet if fear breaks<br />- you can follow your pet without loosing med time, if you see the mana bar increasing, stand up run after your pet for 4 sec and sit down. if you  are sitting again after 6 sec, you will loose no mana compared to sittiing all the time.<br />- keep the mob snared, use another dot as a timer (eg. if you snare with embracing darkness 120 sec and cast directly afterwards splurt 96 sec, you know its time to snare if splurt wears off)<br /><br />combination with other methods:<br />- you can fear a mob, pet taunt off, make aggo like you would aggo kiting. if fear breaks, mob will runn back to you. now just refear if near. nice method of keeping a mob in the area of your choice running forth and back, pet hitting all the time in the back.<br /><br />- root dot one and fear kite another, helps alot to increase exp but needs some concentration. however root is a good idea for adds anyways.<br /><br />what else?<br /><br />- watch adds and keep a root memmed if shit happens<br />- pull your mobs in a region, where usually no add or roamer will appear<br />- watch druids training you)<br /><br /><br />sorry, i just got this idea of the 8 guides. my fear guide was written down in a few minutes, its definately not correct or complete, just a kind of template and example, how a guide should look like.<br /><br />Usul<br /><br />HEY SONY, EEs are just History, like not showing DOT DMG. Just SHOW IT. its all HISTORY, dot dmg and EE. And dont forget CRIT DOTS)<br /><br /><img src="http://frank-neugebauer.bei.t-online.de/quest.jpg" border="0"><br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font>
