                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Not sure if you would class these as other methods, they are really just alterations.<br /><br /> Yo-yo kite<br /> Snare and fear mob (using low level fear) and sick pet on it and a couple of dots (make sure pet not taunting cos you want aggro once fear breaks), once fear breaks let mob come back to you and then fear again. This can work pretty well in a small area where normal fear kiting would cause the mob to travel too far and maybe get adds.<br /><br /> Other I guess would be called charm tanking.<br /> Charm mob and park it (/pet gaurd here) in safe spot, pull mob to it and root and snare mob. Have charmed pet attack it (if you feel confident you can haste charmed mob too) and watch mob die (if its undead slow it too). If your charmed mob breaks charm cast screaming terror to mez it and recharm it (make sure you are standing at max spell range after they are fighting and keep pet targeted). Always make sure mob you are killing is rooted and snared. If your pet is a cleric it will heal itself (yay), if not once it has been in a fight or several fights, and is near death, break charm and root it as soon as possible (from max spell range). Then kill it easily and go find another mob to charm.<br /> Always have a lifetap dd up, snare, root, FD, ST. Good idea to keep harmshield up just incase the faeces really hits the fan.<br /> Another adaption is charm a mob then send it into a pack of mobs, watch pet mobs health, once its at about 2% (or about where you can finish it off with one nuke) break charm with prenerf CoS if you have one,and hit it with a fast nuke to kill it, then FD. Then get up and charm next mob and repeat.<br /><br /><img src="http://www.dinuvian.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/images/PyraelSig.jpg" border="0"><br />Pyrael Soulkeeper<br />Arch Lich of Cohort Chalybeius<br />Cazic-Thule</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
