                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> same but diff to root rot:<br />1. Send in pet<br />2. Snare<br />3. dot x<br />4. dot y<br />5. dot z<br />6. root<br />7. /pet back off<br />8. sit and med<br />9. recast root as needed.<br /><br />Using this method worked well for me, root on ave only had to be recast once every battle.  And by the time mob was dead, i was fm pet was full health.  Sending pet in first gave me time to get off all my dots even at close or confinde quarters, and the pet did some extra damage while I was casting.  I've used this from 50-55, I'm currently 55 and AA hunting and still works fine. The dots were Dooming for snare, Envenomed Bolt, Splurt, and Bond of Death.  I used normal root finding that it worked best for me.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
